  "description": "Join in the festive fun with this funny, rhyming Christmas adventure for preschoolers. With flaps to lift on every page! When Father Christmas sets off to deliver the presents, poor Bear is left behind in the workshop. How will he make it to Tom's house in time for Christmas morning? Lift the flaps s to find out, as he chases Santa's sleigh through icy seas and snowy forests, all the way from the North Pole to Tom's cosy bedroom. With a laugh-out-loud text full of witty rhymes and silly scenarios from Ian Whybrow, author of the much-loved Harry and the Bucket Full of Dinosaurs series, and brilliantly funny illustrations by The Gruffalo illustrator Axel Scheffler. The Christmas Bear: A Push, Pull and Slide Book is a Christmas book with a difference ‚Äì packed full of interactive fun, perfect for little hands. Enjoy more adventures from Axel Scheffler and Ian Whybrow with The Tickle Book and The Bedtime Bear. Read more",
